answer: That's right - the more load you put on the virtual machine (aka instance) the more instances you will need - or the bigger your instance will need to be.  The more efficient your program the more load it can handle for the same size/qty of instances.  However, I'd advise focusing on functionality first, and optimising for performance later, as you can get stuck making something super fast that doesn't actually do the right thing :)

answer: Your code should work for both hard / soft back buttons. But it may be that when your activity is moved to the background, the system runs out of memory (eg due to low RAM on device or too many apps running at once) and force closes your activity.
